<subSubSection box="[858,1372,470,496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="10.[858,1372,470,496]" box="[858,1372,470,496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">
<heading box="[858,1372,470,496]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="(De Vree, 1972)" baseAuthorityName="De Vree" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[858,1372,470,496]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="crassulus" subSpecies="bellieri">
<emphasis box="[858,1174,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">Hypsugo crassulus bellieri</emphasis>
(De Vree, 1972)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="369" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[809,1422,538,1212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">
During this survey, just three specimens of this species were collected in forested habitats on the Liberian side, from 
<quantity box="[1040,1114,607,633]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" unit="m" value="400.0">400 m</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[1150,1246,607,633]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" unit="m" value="1200.0">1,200 m</quantity>
a.s.l. This species had not been previously recorded from Mt Nimba. The taxon 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fahr" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1032,1117,675,701]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bellieri">
<emphasis box="[1032,1117,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">bellieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the Upper 
<collectingCountry box="[809,894,709,735]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">Guinea</collectingCountry>
forest zone and is separated by over 
<quantity metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" unit="km" value="2000.0">2,000 km</quantity>
from the nearest populations of the taxon 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1904" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">crassulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1065,1191,777,803]" name="Cameroon" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
; the two taxa also differ in morphology suggesting that they are specifically distinct (
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J." box="[984,1119,845,871]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" pagination="617 - 619" refId="ref12843" refString="FAHR, J. 2013 f. Pipistrellus crassulus Broad-headed pipistrelle. Pp. 617 - 619, in The mammals of Africa. Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews and bats (M. HAPPOLD and D. C. D. HAPPOLD, eds.). Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Fahr, 2013 
<emphasis box="[1111,1119,845,871]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">f</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
). The conservation status of the taxon 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fahr" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[962,1047,879,905]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bellieri">
<emphasis box="[962,1047,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">bellieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been assessed, but due to continued habitat fragmentation and destruction it may be threatened (
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J." box="[1042,1183,947,973]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" pagination="331 - 332" refId="ref12669" refString="FAHR, J. 2013 c. Rhinolophus guineensis Guinean horseshoe bat. Pp. 331 - 332, in The mammals of Africa. Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews and bats (M. HAPPOLD and D. C. D. HAPPOLD, eds.). Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Fahr, 2013 
<emphasis box="[1170,1183,947,973]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">c</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
). The results of this study support this, as this species was only recorded in old growth forest. In a recent molecular study, 
<bibRefCitation author="DECHER, J. &amp; A. HOFFMANN &amp; J. SCHAER &amp; R. W. NORRIS &amp; B. KADJO &amp; J. ASTRIN &amp; A. MONADJEM &amp; R. HUTTERER" box="[809,1044,1050,1076]" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" pagination="255 - 282" refId="ref12327" refString="DECHER, J., A. HOFFMANN, J. SCHAER, R. W. NORRIS, B. KADJO, J. ASTRIN, A. MONADJEM, and R. HUTTERER. 2015. Bat diversity in the Simandou Mountain Range of Guinea, with the description of a new white-winged vespertilionid. Acta Chiropterologica, 17: 255 - 282." type="journal article" year="2015">
Decher 
<emphasis box="[901,952,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that this species groups with other members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kolenati" authorityYear="1856" box="[1201,1305,1084,1110]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1201,1305,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">Hypsugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, corroborating the results of a karyological study (Volleth 
<emphasis box="[809,859,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">et al</emphasis>
., 2001). We have therefore assigned this species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kolenati" authorityYear="1856" box="[840,944,1186,1212]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[840,944,1186,1212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="369">Hypsugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
